      <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
      <img src="https://www.viven.ch/projects/sv-group-innovation-film-brand-video/01-Inovation_film_VIVEN_Video_Agentur_018.jpg" alt="Video Production in Switzerland: Why Leading Brands Choose Zurich" loading="eager" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:8px 0 26px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover" />

      <h2>Zurich: the heart of Swiss video production</h2>
      <p>It's no accident that the country's biggest companies — banking, industry, fashion, tech — produce their films in Zurich. The city brings together directors, cinematographers, editors and studios that work to cinema standards, not generic "corporate video" ones. That density of talent means a brand can assemble the exact team its project needs, without compromising on quality.</p>

      <h2>Swiss reliability, applied to video</h2>
      <p>For a brand, the biggest risk in a production isn't creative — it's logistical. Budgets that spiral, deadlines that slip, deliverables that fall short. The advantage of producing in Switzerland is the same thing the country is famous for in any industry: a plan, a budget and a date get agreed on, and they get kept. At <a href="/en/services/">Viven</a> we set the timeline before we start, and we stick to it.</p>

      <h2>Cinema craft, working for your brand</h2>
      <p>The difference between a film people remember and one they forget comes down to craft. Viven's founder, Sebastian Cepeda, was the producer of the first Swiss film on Netflix. That same narrative discipline — every shot considered, every minute earning its place — is what we apply to brand, product and employer branding films for clients like UBS, Siemens, Porsche and ON.</p>

      <h2>Results, not just nice footage</h2>
      <p>A film is only worth it if it moves the numbers. A brand video we produced for Siemens tripled visits to its website. That's the standard: Swiss-grade production with a focus on business outcome.</p>

      <p>Have a project in mind? <a href="/en/contact/">Tell us what you're looking for</a> and we'll come back with ideas, timing and a clear quote.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
